'''Lesbian, gay, bisexual, and transgender''' ([[LGBT]]) people in [[Pará]], Brazil enjoy many of the same legal protections available to non-LGBT people. Homosexuality is legal in the state.

==Recognition of same-sex unions==
*On June 28, 2012, in the state of [[Pará]], 28 same-sex couples got married in a ceremony, that took place in [[Belém]].<ref>[http://www.diarioonline.com.br/noticia-208180-para-faz-primeiro-casamento-civil-comunitario-gay.html Diario Online - Pará faz primeiro casamento civil comunitário gay<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>

==LGBT adoption==
'''December 21, 2011''' - the Justice of the city of [[Belém]], [[Pará]] authorized the adoption of a two-year-old child by a lesbian couple.<ref>[http://cenag.uol.com.br/noticias_ler.php?id=Nzc5OQ== Lesbian couple adoption in Pará {{pt icon}}]</ref>

